  "scientific_question": "Does PTEN expression status determine whether drug response in glioma follows structural topology (ODS damper>anchor) or pharmacological addiction (mTOR addiction via PTEN loss)? D3_GBM_stage3 found mTOR was the most effective drug despite being a structural anchor (delta_r=-0.093). The PTEN-loss hypothesis: PTEN deletion creates constitutive PI3K->AKT->mTOR signaling, making cells addicted to mTOR regardless of its structural position. If this is true, the mTOR dominance should be STRONGEST in PTEN-low lines and WEAKEST (or absent) in PTEN-intact lines. In PTEN-intact lines, structural topology should be the dominant determinant: damper drugs (MET, MEK1) should outperform mTOR (anchor).",
