  "hypotheses": [
    {
      "id": "h1",
      "label": "PTEN-loss creates mTOR addiction",
      "statement": "mTOR mean PRISM LFC in PTEN-low glioma lines < mTOR mean PRISM LFC in PTEN-intact glioma lines. mTOR inhibitors kill PTEN-low cells more than PTEN-intact cells. This is the direct test of the PTEN-loss mTOR override mechanism: PTEN deletion -> constitutive PI3K->AKT->mTOR -> mTOR addiction -> cells die readily when mTOR is inhibited. Threshold: difference > 0.10 LFC units (10% more killing in PTEN-low vs intact)."
    },
    {
      "id": "h2",
      "label": "Topology ordering recovers in PTEN-intact lines",
      "statement": "In PTEN-intact glioma lines only: MEK1 mean PRISM LFC < mTOR mean PRISM LFC. MEK1 (structural DAMPER, delta_r=+0.099) kills more than mTOR (structural ANCHOR, delta_r=-0.093) when PTEN-loss addiction is absent. This mirrors the CRC result where MEK1 was the damper and outperformed mTOR (confirmed D3_CRC_v1). If H2 is confirmed: structural topology predicts drug ordering in PTEN-intact GBM, and the PTEN-loss override is the mechanism explaining the H2 denial in the full panel."
    },
    {
      "id": "h3",
      "label": "MET damper ranking in PTEN-intact lines",
      "statement": "In PTEN-intact glioma lines: MET mean PRISM LFC < mTOR mean PRISM LFC. MET is the largest structural damper (delta_r=+0.185). Weaker prediction than H2 (smaller drug class: only crizotinib + cabozantinib), but if confirmed strengthens the damper ordering claim in PTEN-intact GBM."
    },
    {
      "id": "h4",
      "label": "Full r recovery in PTEN-intact",
      "statement": "Spearman r(delta_r, mean LFC) < -0.40 across 6 cytotoxic nodes in PTEN-intact glioma lines. In D3_GBM_stage3 (all glioma): r=-0.371. If PTEN-loss lines are driving the mTOR outlier that breaks topology ordering, removing them should push r below the -0.40 threshold. n=6 nodes (MET, MEK1, AKT1, PI3K, mTOR, EGFR)."
    }
